Help on skill: Wondrous legerdemain.
Usage duration: automatic.
Skill type: special.
Affecting stat(s): skill percent, dexterity, charisma and intelligence.
One might be impressed to see a bard juggling several wickedly sharp axes,
but when one witnesses a Magus Artiste doing the same with firebolts one has
a reason to be truly awed.
While the actual juggling of projectiles is beyond most, each Artiste with
at least some training in the "wondrous legerdemain" is able to counter
hostile projectile magics to a great degree. This talent employs almost
dance-like routines not only for avoiding the projectile but gaining limited
control over it. By expending a slight amount of magical energy, the Artiste
can alter the course of the bolt and potentially launch it back towards its
original caster. As the skill of the Artiste increases they are actually
able to suspend the bolt almost indefinitely by keeping the projectile in
motion but constantly influencing its course, making it appears as if they
were juggling with it. These projectiles can then be thrown at will at a
target.
Being trained in the arts of acrobacy and traditional juggling have been
found to be of benefit.
